!begin_node (!kw [html_doctype])
!html_name cmd_html_doctype

Defines the document type (HTML only).

!begin_xlist [(!TYPEPOSITION)]

!item [(!TYPEPOSITION)] (!COMMAND), (!PREAMBLE)

!item [(!SYNTAX)] (!T)!/html_doctype (!TEXT)(!t)

!item [(!DESCRIPTION)]
This command sets the document type for HTML. (!TEXT) can be one of the
following values:
!begin_blist !compressed
!item [Old]                HTML 3.2
!item [Strict]             HTML 4.01 Strict
!item [Transitional]       HTML 4.01 Transitional
!item [5]                  HTML 5
!item [XHTML Strict]       XHTML Strict
!item [XHTML Transitional] XHTML Transitional
!end_blist

If you use frame mode, the DOCTYPE will be defined automatically.

!item [(!EXISTSSINCE)] Release~6 Patchlevel~16

!end_xlist

(!EXAMPLE)
(!EXAMPLE_BEFORE)
!begin_verbatim
!html_doctype Strict
!end_verbatim
(!EXAMPLE_AFTER)
(!IN_HTML_HEADER)
!begin_preformatted
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01//EN"
        "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd">
!end_preformatted
(!EXAMPLE_END)

!end_node
